Founded in 1908 and former bastion of secular education, the University of Cairo later became a fief of Islamist student groups in the 1970s.
Mr. Morsi made a symbolic swear on Friday on the Tahrir Square, where the uprising that ended the authority regime in Mubarak last year began, and swore to recover the presidential powers which the military council, which replaced the ex-president who was expelled, dismissed.
But by accepting to officially swear before the Court, rather than before the Parliament as it is usual, he tends to the will of the army by showing that the struggle for power is not over.
